<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFBAFFF0A7ADFB33FEC1D993" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADFB33FEB8D8F4" blockId="35.[189,382,1243,1270]" box="[189,382,1243,1270]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFBAFFF0A7ADFB33FEB8D8F4" bold="true" box="[189,382,1243,1270]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A7ADFB33FEB8D8F4" bold="true" box="[189,382,1243,1270]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Natural history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADFAE4FEC1D993" blockId="35.[188,1399,1291,1426]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
All known specimens were collected in a disturbed area, under a zinc sheet. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FFBAFFF0A3DCFAE4FAB7D924" author="Armas L. F." box="[1228,1393,1291,1317]" firstAuthor="Armas" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="55 - 64" part="47" refId="ref145986" refString="Armas L. F. 2010. Nuevos aracnidos de Puerto Rico (Arachnida: Amblypygi, Araneae, Opiliones, Parasitiformes, Schizomida, Scorpiones). Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 47: 55 - 64." title="Nuevos aracnidos de Puerto Rico (Arachnida: Amblypygi, Araneae, Opiliones, Parasitiformes, Schizomida, Scorpiones)" type="journal article" year="2010">Armas (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, of all females collected, six carried egg sacs, suggesting that populations of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFBAFFF0A37FFAC0FAD7D948" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="2010" box="[1135,1297,1327,1353]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezassoi">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A37FFAC0FAD7D948" box="[1135,1297,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">C. perezassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be parthenogenetic. The number of embryos and protonymphs on the females varied between two and seven.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FFBAFFF0A7ADFA55FDF1DA26" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADFA55FEE9D9D5" blockId="35.[189,303,1466,1492]" box="[189,303,1466,1492]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<heading id="5C1D150FFFBAFFF0A7ADFA55FEE9D9D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1466,1492]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A7ADFA55FEE9D9D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1466,1492]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FFBAFFF0A7ADFA06FDF1DA26" blockId="35.[189,1399,1513,1576]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Further comparisons between 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FFBAFFF0A530FA06FD78DA02" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="2010" box="[544,702,1513,1539]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezassoi">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A530FA06FD78DA02" box="[544,702,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">C. perezassoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other Caribbean and Central American species may be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FFBAFFF0A637F9E2FDF6DA29" author="Miranda G. S. &amp; Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Wizen G." box="[295,560,1549,1576]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miranda" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="545 - 559" part="4098" refId="ref151213" refString="Miranda G. S., Giupponi A. P. L. &amp; Wizen G. 2016 b. Two new species of whip spider (Amblypygi): an epigean and a cave dwelling Charinus Simon, 1892 from Belize. Zootaxa 4098 (3): 545 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4098.3.7" title="Two new species of whip spider (Amblypygi): an epigean and a cave dwelling Charinus Simon, 1892 from Belize" type="journal article" year="2016" yearSuffix="b">
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FFBAFFF0A637F9E2FE4CDA26" box="[295,394,1549,1575]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Miranda</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="359E7E71FFBAFFF0A682F9E1FE0ADA26" box="[402,460,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2016b)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
